article.headline: Youngstown St. 76, Loyola of Chicago 71
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) -- Keston Roberts scored 30 points to lead Youngstown State to a 76-71 win over Loyola of Chicago on Saturday. Youngstown State (7-7) came out strong in the first half, shooting 56.3 percent and building a 20-point lead with 1:07 remaining. The Penguins took a 46-29 lead into halftime. Loyola (9-5) battled back in the second half and pulled within three when Majak Kou's 3-pointer with just over a minute to play made it 70-67, but Youngstown State made six of eight free throws down the stretch to pull away from the Ramblers. Kou led the Ramblers with 30 points, including five 3-pointers, and J.R. Blount had 13 points. Leon Young added 11 points and ten rebounds. Quin Humphrey scored 20 points and had 9 rebounds for the Penguins and John Barber had ten points.
